# CHIMERA NEXUS - Quick Install Guide (Windows)

## Problem: scikit-learn needs Microsoft C++ Build Tools

You saw this error because scikit-learn 1.3.0 needs to be compiled from source on Windows, which requires Visual C++.

## Solution: Use the Updated Installer

The new `install_nexus.ps1` script now:
- ✅ Forces precompiled wheels (no compilation needed)
- ✅ Uses stable TensorFlow 2.16.x (has Windows wheels)
- ✅ Installs scikit-learn 1.4.0+ (precompiled available)
- ✅ Makes cloud providers optional
- ✅ Provides clear PyAudio instructions

## Quick Install (Recommended)

```powershell
# Use the modular approach
python -m pip install -r requirements-core.txt

# Then add only what you need:
python -m pip install -r requirements-cloud.txt  # For AWS/Azure/GCP
python -m pip install -r requirements-voice.txt   # For voice interface
```

## Or Install Everything

```powershell
# Run the improved installer
.\install_nexus.ps1
```

