## PyAudio Installation (for Voice)

### Option 1: Download Precompiled Wheel (Easiest)
```powershell
# 1. Download from: https://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#pyaudio
#    File: PyAudio‑0.2.14‑cp312‑cp312‑win_amd64.whl

# 2. Install
python -m pip install PyAudio‑0.2.14‑cp312‑cp312‑win_amd64.whl
```

### Option 2: Install Build Tools
```powershell
# Download and install:
# https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/visual-cpp-build-tools/

# Then:
python -m pip install pyaudio
```

## Troubleshooting

### Issue: "Fatal error in launcher"
This happens when you have multiple Python installations or moved folders.

**Fix:**
```powershell
# Always use python -m pip instead of just pip
python -m pip install <package>

# Or recreate the virtual environment
Remove-Item -Recurse droxai-env
python -m venv droxai-env
& .\droxai-env\Scripts\Activate.ps1
```

### Issue: "Unable to create process"
Your virtual environment path changed (DroxAI → Drox_AI).

**Fix:**
```powershell
# Delete and recreate
Remove-Item -Recurse droxai-env
python -m venv droxai-env
& .\droxai-env\Scripts\Activate.ps1
python -m pip install -r requirements-core.txt
```

### Issue: TensorFlow taking forever to resolve dependencies
The new requirements pin TensorFlow to 2.16.x which resolves faster.

**Fix:**
```powershell
# Install specific version
python -m pip install tensorflow==2.16.2
```

